---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: 'Waxing & Sugaring | D-Essence Wellness',
  description:
    'Smooth, longer-lasting hair removal with waxing or sugaring. Learn the differences, benefits, what to expect, aftercare, and safety.',
  canonical: '/services/waxing-sugaring/',
  type: 'website',
  jsonLd: [
    {
      '@context': 'https://schema.org',
      '@type': 'Service',
      name: 'Waxing & Sugaring',
      serviceType: 'Advanced Skin Care',
      areaServed: 'New Windsor, New York',
      url: 'https://dessencewellness.com/services/waxing-sugaring/',
      provider: {
        '@type': 'MedicalBusiness',
        name: 'D-Essence Wellness',
        address: {
          '@type': 'PostalAddress',
          streetAddress: '871 Blooming Grove Turnpike Suite 102',
          addressLocality: 'New Windsor',
          addressRegion: 'NY',
          postalCode: '12553',
          addressCountry: 'US'
        }
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<BaseLayout seo={seo}>
  <!-- ===== HERO (dark) ===== -->
  <section class="bg-neutral-950 text-white">
    <div class="container pt-28 pb-10 max-w-3xl">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/60">
        <span>Services</span><span class="opacity-40">•</span><span>Advanced Skin Care</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Waxing & Sugaring</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-white/80">
        Choose between classic waxing or gentle sugaring for smooth, longer-lasting results. We’ll guide you to the
        best option for your skin, hair type, and comfort level.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 text-sm">
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Areas</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">Face & body</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Session time</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">10–60+ minutes</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Downtime</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">Minimal</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Result duration</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">~3–4 weeks</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== CONTENT (white) ===== -->
  <section class="bg-white text-neutral-900">
    <div class="container py-12 sm:py-14">

      <!-- Overview -->
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="lg:col-span-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Overview</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700">
            Waxing uses warm or hot wax that adheres to hair (and sometimes skin) and is removed quickly to extract
            hair from the follicle. Sugaring uses a room-temp or gently warmed paste made from sugar, water, and lemon.
            It adheres primarily to hair, is typically removed in the direction of growth, and rinses away with water.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700">
            Key differences include the formula, application temperature, adherence to hair vs. skin, and removal
            direction. Both methods can provide smooth results that last several weeks when performed by trained
            providers.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-5">
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-neutral-50 ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Who it’s for</h3>
            <ul class="mt-3 grid grid-cols-1 gap-2 text-sm text-neutral-700">
              {[
                'Clients seeking longer-lasting hair reduction vs. shaving',
                'Those wanting smoothness for special events or routine upkeep',
                'Sensitive-skin clients who may prefer the gentler feel of sugaring'
              ].map(item => (
                <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                  <span>{item}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Benefits -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Benefits</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <div class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Waxing</div>
            <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-1.5">
              <li>Fast, efficient option for larger areas (legs, arms, back).</li>
              <li>Reliable removal of coarse or dense hair.</li>
              <li>Multiple wax types (soft/hard) to match area sensitivity.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <div class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Sugaring</div>
            <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-1.5">
              <li>Simple, natural ingredients (sugar, water, lemon).</li>
              <li>Typically feels gentler—removed with hair growth.</li>
              <li>Applied lukewarm; easy water cleanup; may reduce ingrowns.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What to expect -->
      <div class="mt-12 grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="lg:col-span-5">
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">What to expect</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700">
            Hair should be long enough for the product to grip (often ~2–3+ mm). Arrive with clean, dry skin and avoid
            heavy lotions or oils beforehand. We’ll discuss sensitivity and perform a quick patch test when helpful.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-7">
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
              <div class="text-sm font-medium text-neutral-900">During treatment</div>
              <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-1.5">
                <li><span class="font-medium">Waxing:</span> applied with hair growth; removed swiftly against growth.</li>
                <li><span class="font-medium">Sugaring:</span> applied against growth; removed with hair growth.</li>
                <li>Technique may vary by area; some methods use strips; others do not.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
              <div class="text-sm font-medium text-neutral-900">Results & timeline</div>
              <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-1.5">
                <li>Smoothness often lasts ~3–4 weeks on average.</li>
                <li>With regular visits, regrowth may become finer over time.</li>
                <li>Session time varies by area: ~10–60+ minutes.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Aftercare -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Aftercare</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <ul class="text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
              <li>Avoid heat (sauna/steam), intense workouts, and sun for 24–48 hours.</li>
              <li>Do not rub or massage the treated area immediately after.</li>
              <li>Use soothing, fragrance-free lotions or aloe if tender.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <ul class="text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
              <li>After 48 hours, begin gentle exfoliation 2–3× weekly to help prevent ingrowns.</li>
              <li>Wear loose clothing to minimize friction.</li>
              <li>Keep skin hydrated with non-comedogenic moisturizers.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Safety -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Safety & risks</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <div class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Common, expected</div>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5">
              <li>Temporary redness or mild swelling</li>
              <li>Localized tenderness or small bruises</li>
              <li>Pinpoint bleeding in sensitive areas</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <div class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Less common</div>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5">
              <li>Prolonged irritation or rash</li>
              <li>Burns (overheated wax)</li>
              <li>Ingrown hairs if exfoliation is neglected</li>
              <li>Skin lifting if removed incorrectly</li>
              <li>Allergy to wax or additives</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <div class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Precautions</div>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5">
              <li>Avoid over wounds, infections, active eczema/psoriasis, or sunburn.</li>
              <li>Use extra caution with thin, bruise-prone skin.</li>
              <li>Recent lasers/peels: allow full recovery before hair removal.</li>
              <li>Known allergies to wax/resins: consider sugaring.</li>
              <li>Visible varicose veins: consult your provider first.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">FAQ</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4">
          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Which hurts more—waxing or sugaring?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              Many find sugaring gentler because it’s removed with the hair growth and adheres less to live skin. Comfort
              varies by area and sensitivity.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">How long do results last?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              Typically around 3–4 weeks, depending on area and hair growth cycles. With routine visits, regrowth may
              appear finer over time.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Is it safe for sensitive skin?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              Yes—many sensitive clients prefer sugaring due to its cooler temperature and hair-focused adherence. We’ll
              tailor technique and aftercare to your skin.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">How often should I book?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              Most clients return every 3–6 weeks depending on area, growth rate, and personal preference.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-neutral-50 ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-6 flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
          <div class="text-sm text-neutral-700">
            Not sure whether waxing or sugaring is right for you? We’ll help you choose.
          </div>
          <a href="/contact-us/" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-neutral-900 text-white px-5 py-2.5 text-sm hover:bg-neutral-800 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-neutral-300">
            Contact Us
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
